Items.description: Luke Scott hit a two-run homer and Josh Bell added a two-run double for his first major league RBIs in a big sixth inning, and the Orioles came back to beat the Angels 6-3 to make Buck Showalter 1-0 as Baltimore's manager.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Ricky Romero baffled the suddenly slumping New York Yankees for the second time this season, and the free-swinging Toronto Blue Jays belted four more home runs in an 8-2 romp Tuesday night.
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Toronto Blue Jays

Items.description: Rookie Neil Walker had three hits and drove in a career-high four runs and the last-place Pirates snapped a five-game losing streak, holding on for a 7-6 victory over the first-place Reds.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. Cincinnati Reds

Items.description: Jeff Francoeur hit a go-ahead solo home run in the ninth inning off Braves closer Billy Wagner and the New York Mets snapped a two-game losing streak with a 3-2 victory over Atlanta on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. New York Mets

Items.description: The Red Sox beat Cleveland 3-1 Tuesday night after a bench-clearing incident.
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Roy Halladay made a triumphant return to the scene of his perfect game, allowing one run in seven innings as the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Florida Marlins 6-1 on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. Philadelphia Phillies

Items.description: Sean Rodriguez and B.J. Upton hit three-run homers as the Tampa Bay Rays beat the Minnesota Twins 6-4 Tuesday night, winning for the 10th time in 11 games and taking over the AL East lead.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Rays vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Chris Narveson pitched 5 2-3 effective innings and also singled in a run, and the Milwaukee Brewers beat the Cubs 4-3 Tuesday night, extending Chicago's losing streak to seven games.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Bud Norris won his fourth game this season and third against the Cardinals and the Astros got career-highs of six RBIs and four hits from rookie Angel Sanchez, stretching their winning streak to seven with an 18-4 rout.
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Jonathan Sanchez limited Colorado to three hits over six innings and the surging Giants beat the Rockies 10-0.
Items.vs: Colorado Rockies vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Mark Reynolds hit a three-run homer in the fourth inning, then was hit in the head by a pitch in the sixth and the Arizona Diamondbacks beat the Washington Nationals 6-1 on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Alex Gordon hit a leadoff double and scored on Greg Blanco's groundout in the ninth inning, and the Kansas City Royals beat the Oakland Athletics 3-2 on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: The Dodgers snapped a six-game losing streak with a 2-1 victory over the Padres on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. San Diego Padres

Items.description: Franklin Gutierrez added a little pop to a night of Seattle small ball with a go-ahead solo homer in the fifth, and the Mariners snapped their seven-game losing streak with a 3-2 victory over the Texas Rangers on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Johnny Cueto dominated the Pirates again over six innings, Paul Janish homered and drove in four runs and the Reds assured themselves of staying atop the NL Central with a 9-4 victory over Pittsburgh.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. Cincinnati Reds

Items.description: Alex Rodriguez hit his milestone 600th home run and the Yankees beat the Blue Jays on Wednesday.
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Toronto Blue Jays

Items.description: The Cubs snapped a seven-game win streak with a rout of the Brewers on Wednesday.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Ubaldo Jimenez won his major league-leading 17th game, Carlos Gonzalez homered twice and the Rockies beat the Giants 6-1.
Items.vs: Colorado Rockies vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Kevin Kouzmanoff hit a tiebreaking, two-run double in the sixth inning to back Brett Anderson, and the Oakland Athletics beat the Kansas City Royals 4-3 on Wednesday to win the three-game series.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Luke Scott homered for the third straight game and the Orioles beat Ervin Santana and the Angels 9-7 to improve to 2-0 under new manager Buck Showalter.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Edwin Jackson won his debut with the White Sox, and Paul Konerko and Carlos Quentin homered as Chicago beat the Detroit Tigers 4-1 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Brian McCann drove in three runs with a homer and two doubles and the Atlanta Braves overcame an injury to starter Kris Medlen to beat the New York Mets 8-3 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. New York Mets

Items.description: Andy Marte hit a three-run homer in a five-run seventh inning, and Justin Masterson pitched five solid innings against his former team on Wednesday night to lead the Cleveland Indians to a 9-1 victory over the Boston Red Sox.
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Rookie Domonic Brown drove in three runs, Kyle Kendrick pitched six effective innings and the Phillies beat the Marlins 7-2.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. Philadelphia Phillies

Items.description: Delmon Young had a tiebreaking RBI single in the 13th inning as the Minnesota Twins beat the Tampa Bay Rays 2-1 on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Rays vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Albert Pujols hit a three-run homer and Chris Carpenter slowed the Houston bats in the St. Louis Cardinals' 8-4 victory over the Astros on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Adam Dunn hit a pair of towering homers and drove in four runs Wednesday night, powering the Washington Nationals to a 7-2 win over the Arizona Diamondbacks.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Vicente Padilla took a no-hit bid into the seventh inning and finished with his fourth career shutout, pitching the Los Angeles Dodgers past the San Diego Padres 9-0 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. San Diego Padres

Items.description: David Murphy hit a go-ahead, three-run home run, Michael Young added his first grand slam in three years and the first-place Texas Rangers beat the lowly Seattle Mariners 11-6 on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Jason Kubel's two-out popup hit a catwalk high above Tropicana Field and fell near the pitcher's mound for a go-ahead single in the ninth inning, a true dome run that sent the Twins past the Rays 8-6.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Rays vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Mark Kotsay's two-run triple in the 11th inning lifted the White Sox over the Tigers on Thursday.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Cesar Izturis singled in the winning run in the ninth inning and the Baltimore Orioles remained unbeaten under new manager Buck Showalter, defeating the Los Angeles Angels 5-4 Thursday night for a three-game sweep.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: James McDonald pitched six shutout innings in his Pittsburgh debut and the Pirates sent the Rockies to their seventh consecutive road loss, 5-1.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Eric Hinske snapped an 0-for-17 hitless streak with a tiebreaking, sixth-inning home run off Tim Lincecum to help the Atlanta Braves to a 3-2 victory over the San Francisco Giants on Thursday night.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Daisuke Matsuzaka pitched eight solid innings and Adrian Beltre hit a grand slam to lead the Boston Red Sox to a 6-2 victory over the Cleveland Indians on Thursday night, earning a split of the four-game series.
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Carlos Ruiz homered leading off the 10th inning, and the Philadelphia Phillies benefited from a bad call to complete a three-game series sweep by beating the Florida Marlins 5-4 Thursday night.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. Philadelphia Phillies

Items.description: Kelly Johnson and Adam LaRoche had three hits each, and Barry Enright overcame two of Washington's four solo homers in six solid innings to lift the Arizona Diamondbacks to an 8-4 win over the mistake-prone Nationals Thursday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Kevin Correia and four relievers combined on San Diego's 5-0 victory over the Los Angeles Dodgers on Thursday night, and the NL West-leading Padres salvaged a split of the four-game series.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. San Diego Padres

Items.description: David Murphy hit his second go-ahead home run in two nights, this one to break through against Felix Hernandez, and Tommy Hunter resumed his excellence as the Texas Rangers cruised to a 6-0 victory over the dreadful Seattle Mariners on Thursday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Bronson Arroyo and the first-place Reds shut out the Cubs on Friday.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Cincinnati Reds

Items.description: Adam Jones singled in the winning run with two outs in the 10th inning, and the Baltimore Orioles extended their unbeaten run under new manager Buck Showalter with a 2-1 victory over the Chicago White Sox on Friday night.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Matt LaPorta homered leading off the bottom of the ninth inning to give the Indians a 7-6 victory over the Twins.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Jered Weaver allowed three hits over seven innings to best Justin Verlander, Torii Hunter hit a two-run homer and tossed a bag of baseballs onto the field after being ejected, and the Los Angeles Angels beat the Detroit Tigers 4-2 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: A dropped infield popup by Francisco Cervelli helped boost Clay Buchholz and the Boston Red Sox to victory in the opener a big four-game series against the New York Yankees.
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Troy Tulowitzki hit a tiebreaking RBI single with two out in the seventh and the Rockies beat the Pirates 6-3 to snap a seven-game road losing streak.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Lyle Overbay doubled home the go-ahead run in the seventh inning, Brett Cecil won for the first time in four starts and the Toronto Blue Jays handed the Tampa Bay Rays their third straight loss, 2-1 Friday night.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: Adam Wainwright pitched a two-hitter for his 16th victory, Albert Pujols homered and the St. Louis Cardinals beat the reeling Florida Marlins 7-0 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Pat Burrell had a sacrifice fly with the bases loaded in the 11th inning and the Giants scored the tying and go-ahead runs without a hit in beating the Braves 3-2.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Carlos Ruiz singled in the go-ahead run during a six-run eighth inning and the Philadelphia Phillies beat the New York Mets 7-5 Friday night for their fifth straight win.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. New York Mets

Items.description: Prince Fielder hit a two-run single in the ninth inning, capping Milwaukee's four-run rally and giving the Brewers a wild 6-5 victory over the Houston Astros on Friday night.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Dan Hudson pitched into the eighth inning to outduel Jon Garland in his second start with Arizona and Adam LaRoche hit his 18th homer, lifting the Diamondbacks past the stumbling San Diego Padres 2-1 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. San Diego Padres

Items.description: Cliff Lee pitched at least eight innings for the 10th straight start, Taylor Teagarden hit a two-run homer and the first-place Texas Rangers built their biggest division lead in 11 years with a 5-1 victory over the Oakland Athletics on Friday night.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Adam Dunn hit a pair of three-run homers off Clayton Kershaw, tying a career high for RBIs, and the Washington Nationals beat the Los Angeles Dodgers 6-3 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Chone Figgins drove in three runs and Ryan Langerhans had three hits, including a home run, to help the Seattle Mariners beat Kansas City's Zack Greinke for the first time, defeating the Royals 7-1 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Drew Stubbs hurt the Chicago Cubs again, hitting a tiebreaking homer in the eighth inning and driving in a pair of runs to lead the surging Cincinnati Reds to a 4-3 victory Saturday.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Cincinnati Reds

Items.description: Blue Jays rookie catcher J.P. Arencibia went 4-for-5 with two home runs Saturday, including one on his first major league pitch, and Toronto slugged eight total in a 17-11 victory over the slumping Rays.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: CC Sabathia outpitched John Lackey, Ramiro Pena drove in two runs while subbing for injured Alex Rodriguez and the New York Yankees stopped their mini-slide by beating the Boston Red Sox 5-2 on Saturday.
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Coco Crisp homered, hit two sacrifice flies and scored twice to back 10-game winner Gio Gonzalez, and the Oakland Athletics beat the first-place Texas Rangers 6-2 on Saturday.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Gavin Floyd allowed two runs in seven innings, and the Chicago White Sox ended Buck Showalter's unbeaten run as manager of the Baltimore Orioles with a 4-2 victory Saturday night.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Carl Pavano pitched seven innings to beat his former team, Joe Mauer had four hits and the Minnesota Twins defeated the Cleveland Indians 7-2 on Saturday.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Scott Kazmir allowed one unearned run in five innings in his return from the disabled list and the Los Angeles Angels routed the slumping Detroit Tigers 10-1 on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Johan Santana pitched 7 1/3 innings and Jeff Francoeur supplied the game's only run with a homer to lead the New York Mets to a 1-0 victory over the Philadelphia Phillies on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. New York Mets

Items.description: Rookie Pedro Alvarez hit a winning three-run homer with two out in the 10th inning to send the Pittsburgh Pirates to a wild 8-7 win over the Colorado Rockies on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Tim Hudson threw eight dominant innings, Troy Glaus hit a two-run single in Atlanta's three-run fourth and the Braves beat the San Francisco Giants 3-0 on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Hanley Ramirez hit a game-winning double in the bottom of the 10th inning to give the Florida Marlins a 5-4 win over the St. Louis Cardinals on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Rickie Weeks hit an inside-the-park home run and George Kottaras added a solo shot to lead the Milwaukee Brewers to a 5-2 win over the Houston Astros on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Chris Young started and ended the game with homers, giving the Arizona Diamondbacks a 6-5 win over the backsliding San Diego Padres on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. San Diego Padres

Items.description: James Loney singled home the winning run with one out in the 10th inning and the Dodgers beat the Nationals 3-2 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Bruce Chen scattered three hits over seven innings and the Kansas City Royals held off the Seattle Mariners 2-1 on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Jim Thome hit a two-run shot for career homer No. 578 and the Minnesota Twins rallied to beat the Cleveland Indians 5-4 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: ohnny Damon drove in three runs, Alex Avila and Will Rhymes had two RBIs apiece and the Detroit Tigers beat the Los Angeles Angels 9-4 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: The Blue Jays' Brandon Morrow lost a no-hit bid with two outs in the ninth inning on an infield single by Evan Longoria, then stuck out his 17th batter of the game to finish off a 1-0 victory over the Tampa Bay Rays on Sunday.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: The weather Sunday was great for fantasy football, not so good for Cardinals-Marlins baseball. The two teams waited out rain in vain for more than four hours before the game was finally postponed.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Derek Lowe pitched into the sixth inning before leaving with an injury and David Ross hit a two-run homer, helping the Atlanta Braves beat the San Francisco Giants 6-3 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Jeremy Guthrie outpitched Mark Buehrle, and the surging Baltimore Orioles beat the Chicago White Sox 4-3 for their fifth win in six games under new manager Buck Showalter.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Raul Ibanez sparked a five-run third inning with a three-run homer, and the Philadelphia Phillies pounded out a dozen hits to support Roy Halladay in a 6-5 victory over the New York Mets on Sunday.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. New York Mets

Items.description: Carlos Gonzalez hit his 25th homer among his four hits, and the Colorado Rockies salvaged a split of a four-game series against last-place Pittsburgh with an 8-4 victory over the Pirates on Sunday.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Casey McGehee hit a three-run homer and Lorenzo Cain drove in the first three runs of his career, helping the Milwaukee Brewers beat the Houston Astros 11-6 on Sunday to complete a three-game sweep.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Joey Votto and Jonny Gomes scored four runs apiece to back a strong start by Travis Wood, and the Cincinnati Reds beat the Chicago Cubs 11-4 on Sunday for their ninth win in 11 games.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Cincinnati Reds

Items.description: Kurt Suzuki hit a tiebreaking sacrifice fly in the seventh inning, Trevor Cahill allowed six hits through eight and the Oakland Athletics beat the first-place Texas Rangers 3-2 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Mat Latos pitched six scoreless innings in a combined three-hitter, Jerry Hairston Jr. created havoc from the leadoff spot and the San Diego Padres beat Arizona 10-1 on Sunday to avoid a three-game sweep by the last-place Diamondbacks.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. San Diego Padres

Items.description: Ted Lilly overcame a rough start to win his second straight outing with Los Angeles, and the Dodgers capitalized on two Washington errors during a four-run first in an 8-3 victory over the Nationals on Sunday.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Jason Vargas allowed one run in six solid innings to win his seventh game at home, and Casey Kotchman's two-run single in the sixth gave Seattle the lead for good in the Mariners' 3-2 win over the Kansas City Royals on Sunday.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Derek Jeter passed Babe Ruth on the career hits list and drove in three runs and Dustin Moseley filled in admirably for an injured A.J. Burnett, leading the New York Yankees to a 7-2 victory over the Boston Red Sox on Sunday night.
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Jon Lester received key help from relievers Daniel Bard and Jonathan Papelbon in ending his career-worst four-game skid, and the Boston Red Sox salvaged a series split by beating the New York Yankees 2-1 Monday.
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Brian Roberts hit his first home run of the season leading off the 10th inning, and the Baltimore Orioles continued their uncanny run of success under new manager Buck Showalter with a 3-2 victory over the Chicago White Sox on Monday night.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Matt Joyce homered and the Tampa Bay Rays snapped their five-game losing streak with a 6-3 win over the Detroit Tigers on Monday night.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: Skip Schumaker hit his first career grand slam during St. Louis Cardinals' biggest inning of the season, supplying more than enough runs for right-hander Chris Carpenter to beat the Cincinnati Reds for the ninth time in a row, 7-3 on Monday night.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Hot-hitting rookie Chris Johnson drove in three runs, including two in Houston's six-run seventh inning, and the Astros took advantage of sloppy play by the Atlanta Braves in a 10-4 win on Monday night.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Stephen Drew hit a two-run single and Ryan Church added a pinch-hit RBI in the 10th inning as the Arizona Diamondbacks rallied off Trevor Hoffman for a 7-4 victory over the Milwaukee Brewers on Monday night.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Bobby Abreu had three hits and drove in four runs to help the Los Angeles Angels defeat the Kansas City Royals 6-4 on Monday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Angels vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Last-place Seattle welcomed new interim manager Daren Brown by getting its first triple play in 15 years in a 3-1 win over the Oakland Athletics on Monday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Oakland Athletics

Items.description: Carlos Zambrano matched his career high with seven walks in his first start since a June 25 dugout blowup and ensuing banishment, and his short-handed Chicago Cubs lost to the San Francisco Giants 4-3 in 11 innings Monday night.
Items.vs: San Francisco Giants vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Felix Pie hit the first of four home runs by Baltimore as the Orioles beat the Indians 14-8 in Buck Showalter's first road game since taking over as manager.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Baltimore Orioles

Items.description: Three Tampa Bay pitchers combined on a four-hitter and the Rays beat the Detroit Tigers 8-0 on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: Andre Ethier had four hits, scored four runs and reached base six times, and Casey Blake and Jay Gibbons hit home runs to lead the Los Angeles Dodgers to a 15-9 battering of the Philadelphia Phillies on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Stephen Strasburg returned from his first trip to the disabled list and turned in the worst start of his sometimes-spectacular rookie season.
Items.vs: Washington Nationals vs. Florida Marlins

Items.description: Mike Lowell hit a go-ahead home run in the eighth inning and the Boston Red Sox beat the Toronto Blue Jays 7-5 on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Yadier Molina jawed with Reds second baseman Brandon Phillips in the first inning, sparking a benches-clearing fight, and the Cardinals followed their catcher's lead to an 8-4 victory that moved St. Louis back into first place in the NL Central.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Mike Pelfrey returned to early-season form, outpitching Ubaldo Jimenez for seven innings, and Jose Reyes hit a sacrifice fly to help the Mets kick off a crucial homestand with a 1-0 win over the Rockies.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Brooks Conrad's two-run homer in the ninth inning powered the Braves to a 4-2 win over the Astros.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: David Murphy's single with the bases loaded in the 10th inning off Mariano Rivera gave the Rangers a 4-3 victory over the Yankees.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Jim Thome hit his 579th homer, Joe Mauer had three more hits and the Twins took sole possession of the AL Central lead by beating the White Sox 12-6.
Items.vs: Chicago White Sox vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Miguel Montero hit a home run to begin the eighth inning and lift the Diamondbacks to a 2-1 victory over the Brewers.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Dan Haren ended a career-long 10-game winless skid with his first victory as an Angel and Peter Bourjos drove in the go-ahead run with a suicide squeeze bunt in the fifth inning as Los Angeles held off the Kansas City Royals 3-1 on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Angels vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Ryan Ludwick hit his first two homers with San Diego, reaching 100 for his career and leading the Padres to a 4-1 victory against the Pittsburgh Pirates on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Felix Hernandez scattered five hits over eight innings and struck out a career-high 13 to lead the Seattle Mariners to a 2-0 victory over the Oakland Athletics on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Oakland Athletics

Items.description: The Cubs battered San Francisco ace Tim Lincecum in an 8-6 win over the Giants on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: San Francisco Giants vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Colby Rasmus hit his first career grand slam, Adam Wainwright dazzled again and the Cardinals beat the Reds 6-1, completing a three-game sweep that changed the standings and made their point.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Ryan Raburn hit a tiebreaking, two-run homer in the sixth inning and the Detroit Tigers held on to beat the Tampa Bay Rays 3-2 Wednesday, avoiding a series sweep.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: Omar Infante drove in the go-ahead run with a 10th-inning double and Brian McCann added insurance with a grand slam later in the inning to give the Braves an 8-2 win over the Astros.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Bobby Abreu hit a walk-off homer in the 10th to lead the Angels past the Royals.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Angels vs. Kansas City Royals

Items.description: Dallas Braden tossed a four-hitter for his fourth career complete game, Mark Ellis hit three doubles and drove in three runs, and the Athletics cruised to a 5-1 win over the Mariners.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Oakland Athletics

Items.description: Brad Bergesen pitched a two-hitter for his first win in nearly three months and the surging Baltimore Orioles beat the Cleveland Indians 3-1 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Baltimore Orioles

Items.description: Roy Oswalt pitched seven impressive innings in his home debut, two relievers finished off the six-hitter and the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Los Angeles Dodgers 2-0 on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Mike Stanton had five hits and four RBIs and Chris Volstad won his third game against the Washington Nationals this season in the Florida Marlins' 9-5 victory Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Washington Nationals vs. Florida Marlins

Items.description: Bill Hall hit two home runs, Adrian Beltre and J.D. Drew also connected and the Boston Red Sox beat Toronto once again, routing the Blue Jays 10-1 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Melvin Mora hit a go-ahead grand slam with two outs in the eighth inning and the Colorado Rockies beat the New York Mets 6-2 on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Marcus Thames hit a long homer then had the go-ahead RBI single in the ninth inning as the New York Yankees rallied from five runs down to beat the Texas Rangers 7-6 on Wednesday night for a split in the two-game series between the division leaders.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: John Danks pitched eight sharp innings and the Chicago White Sox beat Minnesota 6-1 on Wednesday night to move back into a first-place tie in the AL Central with the Twins.
Items.vs: Chicago White Sox vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: The Diamondbacks tied a major league record by hitting four consecutive home runs, with Adam LaRoche, Miguel Montero, Mark Reynolds and Stephen Drew connecting in the fourth inning to beat the Brewers 8-2.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Kevin Correia took a one-hit shutout into the seventh inning and Jerry Hairston Jr. hit a two-run home run to lead the San Diego Padres to an 8-5 victory over the Pittsburgh Pirates on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Pat Burrell hit a go-ahead solo homer in the eighth inning after an earlier two-run single, Aaron Rowand also homered and the San Francisco Giants beat the Chicago Cubs 5-4 on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: San Francisco Giants vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Johan Santana pitched a four-hit shutout to make a closer unnecessary and the Mets beat the Rockies 4-0 after Francisco Rodriguez was arrested on a charge of assaulting his father-in-law at Citi Field.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: The Blue Jays rallied for four runs in the ninth to beat the Red Sox by one on Thursday.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Casey McGehee set a franchise record with his ninth straight hit, going 4-for-4 and leading the Brewers over the Diamondbacks 8-4.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: inch-hitter Andrew Torres hit a bases-loaded single in the bottom of the ninth inning to send the San Francisco Giants into a weekend showdown against San Diego on a high note following an 8-7 victory over the Chicago Cubs on Thursday.
Items.vs: San Francisco Giants vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Ryan Ludwick hit a two-run homer while Jon Garland and three relievers combined on a four-hitter to lead the San Diego Padres to a 3-0 victory Thursday that completed a three-game sweep of the lowly Pittsburgh Pirates.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Rookie Jeanmar Gomez remained unbeaten and the Indians defeated Orioles 4-1, handing Buck Showalter his first road loss as manager.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Baltimore Orioles

Items.description: Carlos Ruiz's game-winning two-run double in the ninth inning capped a frantic rally to help the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Los Angeles Dodgers 10-9 on Thursday night.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Ricky Nolasco rebounded from a rough start by taking a shutout into the seventh inning, Mike Stanton homered for the second consecutive game and the Marlins beat the Nationals 5-0 to complete a three-game sweep.
Items.vs: Washington Nationals vs. Florida Marlins

Items.description: Jason Kubel hit a three-run home run and Francisco Liriano pitched in and out of trouble to help the Minnesota Twins beat the Chicago White Sox 6-1 and move into first place in the American League Central on Thursday night.
Items.vs: Chicago White Sox vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: CC Sabathia picked up his 15th victory, Austin Kearns homered and the New York Yankees held off the Kansas City Royals 4-3 on Thursday night.
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. New York Yankees
